The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Thursday, July 15, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Thursday, July 15, 2004				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Prince Anwar Shah Road and SP Mukherjee Road. Dug up to lay water pipes.				 																Launch				 																																	2004 International Assessment for Indian Schools will be launched at ITC Sonar Bangla, 3 pm.				 																Screening				 																																	Story of Love and The Adventure will be screened, as part of a selective retrospective of Michelangelo Antonioni, organised by Cine Central, at Nandan II, 4 pm and 6 pm, respectively. 				 																Lecture				 																																	B.K. Sarangi will deliver the Nisith Ranjan Ray Memorial Lecture on History of Medical Education in Bengal, organised by Society for Preservation, at Bangla Akademi, 6 pm.				 																Charity				 																																	Aakarshan 2004, an exhibition-cum-sale of household articles, kitchenware, glassware, jewellery, handicrafts and garments, organised by Inner Wheel Club of Calcutta Mahanagar in aid of charities, at Ice Skating Rink, 10 am to 8 pm. 				 																Exhibitions				 																																	Summer Show, an all-India exhibition of paintings and sculptures on display at CIMA Gallery, 2 pm to 7 pm.				 																																	Tamasha, an exhibition of photographs by Sandesh Bhandare, on view at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 2 pm to 7.30 pm.				 																																	An exhibition of Priyanka Guptas paintings will be inaugurated by children of an NGO at INOX, City Centre, at 5 pm.
